<subSubSection id="C31B6527FFD5FFF72DD9F85DC99E66AF" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BBE36ACFFD5FFF72DD9F85DC99E66AF" blockId="21.[151,1436,1931,2037]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis id="B975EABEFFD5FFF72DD9F85DCA4166C7" bold="true" box="[151,281,1931,1957]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
These small specimens (about 4.0 mm) are conveniently distinguished from congeners by having two small black setal tufts near the elytral apex.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C31B6527FFD5FFF42D88F80DCF6D60A8" lastPageId="22" lastPageNumber="23" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BBE36ACFFD5FFF42D88F80DCF7A6018" blockId="21.[151,1436,1931,2037]" lastBlockId="22.[151,1436,152,578]" lastPageId="22" lastPageNumber="23" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis id="B975EABEFFD5FFF72D88F80DCA396697" bold="true" box="[198,353,2011,2037]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Description:</emphasis>
Length 
<quantity id="4CF99B49FFD5FFF72C8FF80DC96A6697" box="[449,562,2011,2037]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.2" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" unit="mm" value="4.2">4. 2 mm</quantity>
; width 
<quantity id="4CF99B49FFD5FFF72FDAF80DC9A06697" box="[660,760,2011,2037]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" unit="mm" value="1.3">1.3 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis id="B975EABEFFD5FFF72E47F80DC8126696" box="[777,842,2011,2036]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Form</emphasis>
: Short oblong rectangulate. 
<emphasis id="B975EABEFFD5FFF729E1F80DCE6B6696" box="[1199,1331,2011,2036]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Integument</emphasis>
: Mostly brown, cranial vertex with two brown setal tufts, legs yellow and with brown infuscations, elytra admixture of light brown and dark brown regions, elytral setae yellow, dark brown, or black, two black setal tufts near the elytral apex. 
<emphasis id="B975EABEFFD6FFF42C7FFF3ECA286063" box="[305,368,232,257]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Head</emphasis>
: Eyes large, very convex; vertex between eyes broad. 
<emphasis id="B975EABEFFD6FFF42EB7FF3ECF156063" box="[1017,1101,232,257]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Thorax</emphasis>
: Pronotal side margins with slightly-developed tubercle, anterior transverse depression not prominent, disc roughly sculptured and with coarse punctations; elytral side margins parallel to posterior four-fifths, then acutely rounded to apex; disc subcorrugated and coarsely punctate. 
<emphasis id="B975EABEFFD6FFF42F1FFEB6C9E7601B" box="[593,703,352,377]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Abdomen</emphasis>
: Female pygidium transverse.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBE36ACFFD6FFF42D88FE51C92D60C0" blockId="22.[151,1436,152,578]" box="[198,629,391,418]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis id="B975EABEFFD6FFF42D88FE51CA1D60C3" bold="true" box="[198,325,391,417]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Variation:</emphasis>
One specimen examined.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBE36ACFFD6FFF42D88FE79CF6D60A8" blockId="22.[151,1436,152,578]" box="[198,1077,431,458]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis id="B975EABEFFD6FFF42D88FE79CAC860AB" bold="true" box="[198,400,431,457]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Natural history:</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus id="54BA880EFFD6FFF42C83FE66C96B60A8" box="[461,563,432,458]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">holotype</typeStatus>
specimen was collected in June, at 
<quantity id="4CF99B49FFD6FFF42E9BFE66CF6960A8" box="[981,1073,432,458]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.646" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" unit="m" value="1646.0">1646 m</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C31B6527FFD6FFF42D88FE01C8206090" box="[198,888,471,498]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BBE36ACFFD6FFF42D88FE01C8206090" blockId="22.[151,1436,152,578]" box="[198,888,471,498]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis id="B975EABEFFD6FFF42D88FE01CA8C6093" bold="true" box="[198,468,471,497]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Distribution (Map 2):</emphasis>
Known only from the 
<typeStatus id="54BA880EFFD6FFF42FAEFE0EC84A6090" box="[736,786,472,498]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">type</typeStatus>
locality.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C31B6527FFD6FFF42D88FE29C87B6320" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BBE36ACFFD6FFF42D88FE29C87B6320" blockId="22.[151,1436,152,578]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis id="B975EABEFFD6FFF42D88FE29CA0F637B" bold="true" box="[198,343,511,537]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Etymology:</emphasis>
The specific epithet is a Latin compound name formed from 
<emphasis id="B975EABEFFD6FFF42965FDD6CF1A637B" box="[1067,1090,512,537]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">bi</emphasis>
(= two) and 
<emphasis id="B975EABEFFD6FFF42994FDD6CE78637B" box="[1242,1312,512,537]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">barba</emphasis>
(= beard). It refers to the two black setal tufts near the elytra apex.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
